		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">psycopathicteen wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Am I the only one to notice the incorrectly shaded checkerboard squares?</div><br />You mean right under the grass? I believe the palettes are set up so that green and brown can't be in the same attribute area, so everything immediately below the grass must be black. I don't think it's very noticeable when the ground is straight as in this mock-up, but I did question how it would look on slopes, which would need far more black pixels.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
